00999 void operator_wrapper(wmOperatorType *ot, void *userdata);
01000 void macro_wrapper(wmOperatorType *ot, void *userdata);
01001 
01002 static char _operator_idname[OP_MAX_TYPENAME];
01003 static char _operator_name[OP_MAX_TYPENAME];
01004 static char _operator_descr[RNA_DYN_DESCR_MAX];
01005 static StructRNA *rna_Operator_register(Main *bmain, ReportList *reports, void *data, const char *identifier,
01006                                         StructValidateFunc validate, StructCallbackFunc call, StructFreeFunc free)
01007 {
01008     wmOperatorType dummyot = {NULL};
01009     wmOperator dummyop = {NULL};
01010     PointerRNA dummyotr;
01011     int have_function[7];
01012 
01013     /* setup dummy operator & operator type to store static properties in */
01014     dummyop.type = &dummyot;
01015     dummyot.idname = _operator_idname; /* only assigne the pointer, string is NULL'd */
01016     dummyot.name = _operator_name; /* only assigne the pointer, string is NULL'd */
01017     dummyot.description = _operator_descr; /* only assigne the pointer, string is NULL'd */
01018     RNA_pointer_create(NULL, &RNA_Operator, &dummyop, &dummyotr);
01019 
01020     /* clear in case they are left unset */
01021     _operator_idname[0] = _operator_name[0] = _operator_descr[0] = '\0';
01022 
01023     /* validate the python class */
01024     if (validate(&dummyotr, data, have_function) != 0)
01025         return NULL;
01026 
01027     {   /* convert foo.bar to FOO_OT_bar
01028          * allocate the description and the idname in 1 go */
01029 
01030         /* inconveniently long name sanity check */
01031         {
01032             char *ch = _operator_idname;
01033             int i;
01034             int dot = 0;
01035             for (i = 0; *ch; i++) {
01036                 if ((*ch >= 'a' && *ch <= 'z') || (*ch >= '0' && *ch <= '9') || *ch == '_') {
01037                     /* pass */
01038                 }
01039                 else if (*ch == '.') {
01040                     dot++;
01041                 }
01042                 else {
01043                     BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR,
01044                                 "registering operator class: '%s', invalid bl_idname '%s', at position %d",
01045                                 identifier, _operator_idname, i);
01046                     return NULL;
01047                 }
01048 
01049                 ch++;
01050             }
01051 
01052             if (i > ((int)sizeof(dummyop.idname)) - 3) {
01053                 BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "registering operator class: '%s', invalid bl_idname '%s', "
01054                             "is too long, maximum length is %d", identifier, _operator_idname,
01055                             (int)sizeof(dummyop.idname) - 3);
01056                 return NULL;
01057             }
01058 
01059             if (dot != 1) {
01060                 BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR,
01061                             "registering operator class: '%s', invalid bl_idname '%s', must contain 1 '.' character",
01062                             identifier, _operator_idname);
01063                 return NULL;
01064             }
01065         }
01066         /* end sanity check */
01067 
01068         {
01069             int idlen = strlen(_operator_idname) + 4;
01070             int namelen = strlen(_operator_name) + 1;
01071             int desclen = strlen(_operator_descr) + 1;
01072             char *ch;
01073             /* 2 terminators and 3 to convert a.b -> A_OT_b */
01074             ch = MEM_callocN(sizeof(char) * (idlen + namelen + desclen), "_operator_idname");
01075             WM_operator_bl_idname(ch, _operator_idname); /* convert the idname from python */
01076             dummyot.idname = ch;
01077             ch += idlen;
01078             strcpy(ch, _operator_name);
01079             dummyot.name = ch;
01080             ch += namelen;
01081             strcpy(ch, _operator_descr);
01082             dummyot.description = ch;
01083         }
01084     }
01085 
01086     /* check if we have registered this operator type before, and remove it */
01087     {
01088         wmOperatorType *ot = WM_operatortype_find(dummyot.idname, TRUE);
01089         if (ot && ot->ext.srna)
01090             rna_Operator_unregister(bmain, ot->ext.srna);
01091     }
01092 
01093     /* XXX, this doubles up with the operator name [#29666]
01094      * for now just remove from dir(bpy.types) */
01095 
01096     /* create a new operator type */
01097     dummyot.ext.srna = RNA_def_struct(&BLENDER_RNA, dummyot.idname, "Operator");
01098     RNA_def_struct_flag(dummyot.ext.srna, STRUCT_NO_IDPROPERTIES); /* operator properties are registered separately */
01099     dummyot.ext.data = data;
01100     dummyot.ext.call = call;
01101     dummyot.ext.free = free;
01102 
01103     dummyot.pyop_poll = (have_function[0])? operator_poll: NULL;
01104     dummyot.exec =      (have_function[1])? operator_execute: NULL;
01105     dummyot.check =     (have_function[2])? operator_check: NULL;
01106     dummyot.invoke =        (have_function[3])? operator_invoke: NULL;
01107     dummyot.modal =     (have_function[4])? operator_modal: NULL;
01108     dummyot.ui =            (have_function[5])? operator_draw: NULL;
01109     dummyot.cancel =        (have_function[6])? operator_cancel: NULL;
01110     WM_operatortype_append_ptr(operator_wrapper, (void *)&dummyot);
01111 
01112     /* update while blender is running */
01113     WM_main_add_notifier(NC_SCREEN|NA_EDITED, NULL);
01114 
01115     return dummyot.ext.srna;
01116 }
